ಇಂದು ’ವಿಶ್ವ ಪುಸ್ತಕ ದಿನ’ ಕೊರೊನ ಕತ್ತಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಜ್ಞಾನದ ಬೆಳಕು ಕಾಣಲು ಪುಸ್ತಕಕ್ಕಿಂತ ಸಂಗಾತಿ ಬೇರೊಂದಿಲ್ಲ. ಓದುವ ಹವ್ಯಾಸ ಹೆಚ್ಚಿಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳಿ, ಇತರರೂ ಪುಸ್ತಕ ಓದುವ ಅಭಿರುಚಿ ಬೆಳಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳಲು ಪ್ರೇರೇಪಿಸಿ. ಆ ಮೂಲಕ ನಮ್ಮ ಸಾಹಿತ್ಯ ಕ್ಷೇತ್ರವನ್ನು ಶ್ರೀಮಂತಗೊಳಿಸಲು ಸಂಕಲ್ಪ ತೊಡಿ.

A vaccine for COVID-19 could help restore life to normal. But it's not around the corner. @DrKellyHenning explains:

I couldn't agree more, @JohnFeinblatt. Thanks to @shannonrwatts and millions of @MomsDemand volunteers, gun safety laws are being passed in red, blue and purple states across the country — and we're just getting started.

The @BloombergDotOrg initiative to work with New York State to develop a contact tracing program will be hard work. But I know, because we’re working with @NYGovCuomo, @ResolveTSL, and @JohnsHopkinsSPH, that we’ll succeed. Now is the time to rely on each other.

New York is in need. But New Yorkers can rely on one another. And they can rely on @NYGovCuomo. I'm glad to announce that @BloombergDotOrg is committing to partner with New York State to build a contact tracing program. #NewYorkTough

Today is #EarthDay, and we are facing two global catastrophes: #COVID19 and climate change. But we shouldn’t have to choose which battle to fight. By building a 100% green economy, we can ensure cleaner air and a safer future for our cities. Let’s invest in our future.

The fight against climate change, like the fight against #COVID19, has proven that when the federal government fails, local action can make a difference. On this 50th anniversary of #EarthDay, we look back at what local climate action can achieve:

Now more than ever, the world needs to come together. Going it alone just won’t work. The @BloombergDotOrg Partnership for Healthy Cities is bringing global city leaders together to ensure they have the support they need to take action:

Cities are facing a crisis that has strained hospitals, caused mass unemployment, and upended life itself. But if we work together, as @DrHowardKoh told the @BloombergDotOrg virtual convening of mayors, we will get through this together.

Grand Rapids @MayorBliss is showing us what leadership looks like. She’s helped transform breweries to make hand sanitizer, while helping small businesses stay open. I’m glad @BloombergDotOrg can support mayors across this country as they lead us through this crisis.

Contact tracing isn’t only how we stop the spread, it’s how we reopen the country. @DrKellyHenning reminds us that we’ve done it before with diseases like TB, but never on a national scale. It requires effective tools & a trained force of testers to begin the road to recovery.

This virus has changed the way we live. And the nonprofits that so often help those in need, are in need themselves. The NYC COVID-19 Response & Impact Fund is helping these programs, like @MindBuildersCAC, continue their vital work. I’m proud @BloombergDotOrg can play a part.

Earlier this year, I visited the Oklahoma City Bombing Memorial. We'll always remember that day 25 years ago & the lives of those who were killed. As we now face this unprecedented crisis, I know the same tenacious spirit that brought us together then will pull us through again.

In support of @GlblCtzn’s #TogetheratHome initiative, @BloombergDotOrg is giving $8 million to the @WHO COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund to help health care workers on the frontlines. Thanks for spreading the word, @JimmyFallon. https://bloombg.org/2VCweEk

The @WHO is a global force for good. If we want to get through this together, we have to work together. Thank you @DrTedros, @GlblCtzn, and @LadyGaga for bringing us all together today. #TogetherAtHome
